                        "content": "The nurse is reviewing the pathophysiology of influenza and the various strains of the disease. The nurse would correctly identify H3N2 as which type of influenza?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "c2472dbaf30269ec1d4a4af474a31869",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Understanding 理解",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nInfluenza is divided into four different serotypes: A, B, C, and D. Influenza A is further delineated into different strains based on two viral surface proteins: hemagglutinin (H) and neuraminidase (N). An example of influenza A is H1N1, otherwise known as the swine flu. Therefore, option 1 is the correct answer, as influenza A viruses are further named based on the H and N proteins.",
                        "id": "18f5922576bb4648b73a95fb20ab01a5",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "c6a1ba19b4e544a1be389862c2bf42b5",
                                "content": "“Influenza has a rapid symptom onset, while common cold symptoms appear gradually.”"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "6042479e41124f4a8b7ddd2d52131e71",
                                "content": "“It is very common to have a fever with the common cold, while a fever with influenza is rare.”"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "ed11b989ab33425aa444494e7268205f",
                                "content": "“Severe muscle pains and aches are associated with the common cold and are rare with influenza.”"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "ddcc03d8bbd04c6aab03a78ac01c7cf0",
                                "content": "“There is an annual vaccination for viral rhinitis, which decreases the severity of the common cold.”"
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
                                    "isRight": "1",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
