                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse is assessing a client presenting with a temperature of 103° F (39.4° C), severe muscle aches, and headache who states that the symptoms “came out of nowhere.” The client states that other family members in the home are having similar symptoms. The client’s lung sounds are clear to auscultation, the sinuses are nontender to palpation, there is no nasal drainage, the tympanic membranes are pearly gray bilaterally, the tonsils are without redness or exudates, and the anterior and posterior cervical lymph nodes are negative for lymphadenopathy. Which condition would the nurse suspect?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nInfluenza is a viral illness characterized by the sudden onset of high fever ranging from 103° F to 104° F (39.4° C to 40° C) with severe myalgia. Lung sounds are often clear to auscultation, and the client may or may not have a headache, sore throat, or nasal congestion. Option 1 is not as likely since the client’s sinuses are nontender to palpation and there is no nasal drainage present. Option 3 is unlikely due to the physical exam finding that the tonsils are free of redness and exudates. Option 4 is not as likely as high fevers are rare with viral rhinitis. Therefore, option 2 is correct.",
                        "id": "8267d3dace304c7a9c3f89342bdc4ef5",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "00158e59b28242cabaedf1880be1cf63",
                                "content": "“I’ll make sure I’m drinking plenty of fluids.”"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "37f5bdfca8dc440685d84dbcb08136e8",
                                "content": "“I need to avoid close contact with my family members and wash my hands frequently.”"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "743063d8bd6249aeb98ffa75c9688151",
                                "content": "“I can take either ibuprofen or acetaminophen to help with my aches and pains, as well as my fever.”"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "53e46bc91d954fa9ba639019078eb6ba",
                                "content": "“I don’t understand why the primary health care provider (PHCP) did not give me a prescription for an antiviral medication. I feel really sick and I need it!”"
                            }
                        ],
